                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry> Account ID </entry>
                            <entry> 1-16 character string </entry>
                            <entry> Mandatory </entry>
                            <entry> Indicates which account to provision. MSISDN/MDN for Subscriber
                                Account Type or Account ID for Group Account. </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry> Bucket ID </entry>
                            <entry> String </entry>
                            <entry> Mandatory </entry>
                            <entry> Defines the id of the bucket to be required or "ALL" buckets.
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry> Bucket Message Info </entry>
                            <entry> boolean </entry>
                            <entry> Optional </entry>
                            <entry> Indicates whether to return the residual balance text message
                                that can be sent to subscribers to provide bucket information such
                                as carry-over bucket value and expiration date. It can only be set
                                to "Y" when the Account Type is Subscriber. When it is set to "Y",
                                only the message information is returned. When it is set to "N",
                                message information is not included. </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry> Real Time Update </entry>
                            <entry> String </entry>
                            <entry/>
                            <entry> Indicate whether to trigger RAR to update in real-time the
                                values counters of subscribers. </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
